<br>
    Some of the highest aggro spells in the game are spells that magicians cannot wield.  Mesmerize, Tash, Snare, Stun are all excellent taunt mechanisms.  The highest aggro spells we have, on the other hand, are nukes, and the bigger the better.......  BUT big nukes suck your mana down FAST.  Really, though, unless you plan on blowing half a mana bar or more competing with your pet for aggro (and unless you have a horse, you aren't gaining any benefit from meditating), this method can be problematic at best.<br>
<br>
    A couple things I can add that may help you.  Using a combination of aggro kiting and reclaim chaining will address any mana efficiency issues, and a fresh pet will give you that much of a head start before the mob (inevitably) turns on your pet.  Boots of Bladecalling could be useful for adding more hate just when the mob turns on the pet, and will allow the next pet to do more damage before the mob gets annoyed at Jobaner again.  Snare glands can be helpful, but they are limited in charges (10).<br>
<br>
    Contrary to virtually every other class in the game when solo, magicians solo most efficiently by limiting the aggro to themselves.  Also, we are uniquely equipped to do just that.  There is likely no mob in the game we could effectively solo using kiting methods that we couldn't go and duo with another magician using either regular pet chaining tactics, or IR chaining.<br>
<br>
    I have had extremely limited success with aggro kiting, and I doubt I'm alone in this.  I wish you luck and success, and if you figure out something that I haven't, by all means post it here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=pissed1vi2soe>Pissed1VI2SOE</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#333333>(8/8/02 6:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  comment</span><hr size=1> Was agro kiting last night, my bard and necro w/ pet.  Here's how I kept agro 100% of the time with the pet taunt on and pet doing massive damage, while I was just tossing in low nuks.<br>
<br>
Sing the only bard dd to get mobs attention (alot less dmg than a pet hits for 24dmg atm), sing selo's to drag him to the pet.  Sing snare when you get close, then twist snare and dd.  Pet was owning the mob doubling for 36's (that I saw), while I was only twisting 1 nuke and 1 snare.  Snare is a huge agro, the bad thing about a druid is that their snare lasts sooooo long and they lose agro after about 100 damage is done.  Yeah I could have thrown in 2 dd's per snare but then I would chance losing agro and/or getting hit.<br>
<br>
xp was actually pretty good, since I never had to sing heal or mana, necro is lblue to me his pet was way green and mobs were even cons, took about 3 minutes/kill but it gave better xp than me kiting 12  low blues (not light blues, just low blues) for 3 minutes then having to sing heal and mana for 2 more.  It just hurts toooo much to take hits from xp mobs as a bard at least. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucjell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cjell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(8/13/02 8:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: comment</span><hr size=1> I have been doing this a fair amount in GD lately.  I will pull with a bolt spell from long range, manage to get another bolt spell launched before the giant arrives.  Then, while on horse I just run about...and by the time the giant turns his attention to the pet, it is almost dead.  <br>
<br>
Before fight, I will of course cast expedience on the pet, so that he is able to keep up with the giant.  Works better if the pet is sow'ed with a potion, but that makes it a bit more costly.  Also, it is a good idea to run in straight lines forming a box pattern if possible, rather then a circle, at least with giants and their huge aggro range.  I guess it is just the fact that my main is a 56 bard, that I just love to kite stuff...hehe<br>
